{
  "openapi": "3.1.0",
  "info": {
    "title": "Aide axum Open API for ranal",
    "summary": "Rust compiler repository analyzer",
    "description": "# Ranal\n\n**Ranal** is a simple, efficient tool for analyzing GitHub repositories primarly Rust repository.\nTrack everything about contributors, issues, and repository activity — all written in Rust.\n\n## Features (Planned)\n\n- Analyze contributor activity.\n- Track open and closed issues.\n- Gather repository statistics like commits, pull requests, and more.\n\n## Configuration\n\nCreate a `.env` file in the `backend` directory from the provided `.env.example` file and fill in\nthe required environment variables.\n\n## Database\n\n### Setup via Docker\n\nYou can use [docker compose](./docker-compose.yml) to run a postgres database.\nYou can also run postgres database locally.\n\n```bash\ndocker compose up -d\nsqlx migrate run\n```\n\n### Setup via local Postgres\n\nMake sure you have a running Postgres instance.\nCreate a database named `ranal` (or any name you prefer) and set up the connection string in the\n`.env` file.\n\nNow you can create database `sqlx database create` and run migrations using `sqlx migrate run`.\n*database will be created as is in .nev file*\n\n*if you dont have sqlx-cli installed, you can do it by\nrunning: ``cargo install sqlx-cli --features native-tls``*\n\n## Usage\n\nThis command will fill the database with last 500 pull requests as demonstration. *(Number is number\nof pages to fetch, each page contains 100 items)*\n\n```bash\ncargo run -- analyze --sync 5\n```\n\nIf you have all the data you want you can run the server:\n\n```bash\ncargo run -- serve\n```\n\nOf course, you can always run command or subcommand with `--help` to see all available options.\n\nThen you can access the API docs at `http://localhost:7878/docs`.\n\n[//]: # (Link to database schema [here]&#40;https://dbdiagram.io/d/6791134c37f5d6cbeb969453&#41; TODO add link when ready)\n\n## TODO\n\n- add tests\n\n## License\n\nThis project is licensed under the MIT License. See the LICENSE file for details.",
    "version": ""
  },
  "paths": {
    "/api/pr/reviewers": {
      "get": {
        "tags": [
          "PR"
        ],
        "description": "Get users who made reviews on a specific file/path within a date range",
        "parameters": [
          {
            "in": "query",
            "name": "file",
            "description": "File path to filter reviews, example = \"src/lib.rs\", exmple = \"src/\"",
            "required": true,
            "schema": {
              "description": "File path to filter reviews, example = \"src/lib.rs\", exmple = \"src/\"",
              "type": "string"
            },
            "style": "form"
          },
          {
            "in": "query",
            "name": "from_date",
            "description": "Start date (ISO 8601). default Now, example = \"2025-01-01\"",
            "schema": {
              "description": "Start date (ISO 8601). default Now, example = \"2025-01-01\"",
              "type": [
                "string",
                "null"
              ],
              "format": "date"
            },
            "style": "form"
          },
          {
            "in": "query",
            "name": "last_n_days",
            "description": "Number of days to look back, default 7, example = 30",
            "schema": {
              "description": "Number of days to look back, default 7, example = 30",
              "type": [
                "integer",
                "null"
              ],
              "format": "int64"
            },
            "style": "form"
          },
          {
            "in": "query",
            "name": "pagination",
            "schema": {
              "anyOf": [
                {
                  "$ref": "#/components/schemas/Pagination"
                },
                {
                  "type": "null"
                }
              ]
            },
            "style": "form"
          },
          {
            "in": "query",
            "name": "repository",
            "description": "Repository identifier to filter reviews, example = \"owner/repo\"",
            "required": true,
            "schema": {
              "description": "Repository identifier to filter reviews, example = \"owner/repo\"",
              "type": "string"
            },
            "style": "form"
          }
        ],
        "responses": {
          "200": {
            "description": "",
            "content": {
              "application/json": {
                "schema": {
                  "$ref": "#/components/schemas/PaginatedResponse_for_Contributor"
                }
              }
            }
          },
          "500": {
            "description": "",
            "content": {
              "application/json": {
                "schema": {
                  "type": "string"
                }
              }
            }
          }
        }
      }
    },
